[30;1m1220 | [0m[35m    - It also allows publishers with bandwidth concerns to control the size of each batch published.[0m
[30;1m1221 | [0m[35m- Added new configuration parameters for exponential delay between retry operations.[0m
[30;1m1222 | [0m[35m    - `retry_total`: The total number of attempts to redo the failed operation.[0m
[30;1m1223 | [0m[35m    - `backoff_factor`: The delay time factor.[0m
[30;1m1224 | [0m[35m    - `backoff_max`: The maximum delay time in total.[0m

[30;1m379 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m380 | [0m[35m`EventHubConsumerClient` is a high level construct which allows you to receive events from multiple [0m
[30;1m381 | [0m[35mand load balance with other consumers using the same Event Hub and consumer group.[0m
[30;1m382 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m383 | [0m[35mThis also allows the user to track progress when events are processed using checkpoints.[0m

[30;1m282 | [0m[35m> **Note:** V1 checkpoints are not compatible with V5 checkpoints.[0m
[30;1m283 | [0m[35mIf pointed at the same blob, consumption will begin at the first message.[0m
[30;1m284 | [0m[35mV1 checkpoint json in the respective blobs can be manually converted (per-partition) if needed.[0m
[30;1m285 | [0m[35mIn V1 checkpoints (sequence_number and offset) are stored in the format of json along with ownership[0m
[30;1m286 | [0m[35mas the content of the blob, while in V5, checkpoints are kept in the metadata of a blob and the meta[0m

[30;1m281 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m283 | [0m[35mIf pointed at the same blob, consumption will begin at the first message.[0m
[30;1m284 | [0m[35mV1 checkpoint json in the respective blobs can be manually converted (per-partition) if needed.[0m
[30;1m285 | [0m[35mIn V1 checkpoints (sequence_number and offset) are stored in the format of json along with ownership[0m
[30;1m286 | [0m[35mas the content of the blob, while in V5, checkpoints are kept in the metadata of a blob and the meta[0m

[30;1m323 | [0m[35mdiary. Messages that live longer than their expiration time will be discarded[0m
[30;1m324 | [0m[35m     (or dead lettered). When a message is transmitted by an intermediary that was received[0m
[30;1m325 | [0m[35m     with a ttl, the transmitted message's header SHOULD contain a ttl that is computed as the[0m
[30;1m326 | [0m[35m     difference between the current time and the formerly computed message expiration time,[0m
[30;1m327 | [0m[35m     i.e., the reduced ttl, so that messages will eventually die if they end up in a delivery loop.[0m

[30;1m329 | [0m[35m    :ivar durable: Durable messages MUST NOT be lost even if an intermediary is unexpectedly termina[0m
